page.title: 19BRAMFORD SPEKE
page.content: { My name is Alison. The school I goto is Bramford Speke primary school.There are 19 infants and 20 juniors.As you come out of the main gate (by the infants class room,which separate from our classroom) there is a tree by our school.It was planted by Mr Stenor in 1964. It is a Quercus Rubra (red oak).There are two roads one goes to the left and one goes straight on. If you take the one that goes straight on you come to a old mass chapel. It still gets a big congregation each week.It was built in 1894.There are two semidetached cottages.The place is called St End. Opposite there is a big house which has enormous grounds.The road is called Chapel Road, because of the chapel.There are two pumps by the cottages.Then there is a lane that goes straight on and out of Brampford Speke.
